NAME
	playerget - get the playerfile of a player

SYNOPSYS
	playerget <name>

ACCESS CLASS
	Apart arches and keepers only people who have been granted access
	with the 'playeraccess' command can use this command.

DESCRIPTION
	With this command the playerfile of a mortal player can be copied
	from the secured directory for the playerfiles to the directory
	~/private/players in the wizards home directory.

ARGUMENTS
	<name> 	the name of the mortal player whose file to copy.

SEE ALSO
	playeraccess, playerput
